# 4c8dc9464e7d440a9eff602501da7d93
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/managing-logs.en.rst:83
msgid "Rolling Logs"
msgstr ""

# f2251c472d104689b571752bab8d4e5a
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/managing-logs.en.rst:85
msgid ""
"|TS| provides automatic log file rolling. At specific intervals during "
"the day or when log files reach a certain size, |TS| closes its current "
"set of log files and opens new log files. Depending on the amount of "
"traffic your servers are exposed to, you may find that increasing the "
"frequency of log rolling is beneficial, or even necessary, to maintain "
"manageable log file sets. |TS| nodes processing moderately high levels of"
" traffic may want to start by rolling logs every six hours, and adjusting"
" from there."
msgstr ""

# c4ae4e896cda4359b609f3c0f179f2df
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/managing-logs.en.rst:93
msgid "Log file rolling offers the following benefits:"
msgstr ""

# 0ad8b873724547958d6553013cb5c29d
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/managing-logs.en.rst:95
msgid ""
"It defines an consistent interval over which log analysis can be "
"performed."
msgstr ""

# 1f513317c0664aef9cfeb6f4ac3ce1a9
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/managing-logs.en.rst:97
msgid ""
"It keeps any single log file from becoming too large and helps to keep "
"the logging system within the specified space limits."
msgstr ""

# e0dd2bac81e94afea5bca1c2591d0ce4
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/managing-logs.en.rst:100
msgid ""
"It provides an easy way to identify files that are no longer being used "
"so that an automated script can clean the logging directory and run log "
"analysis programs."
msgstr ""

# 93983fcf7957419f804832cebe38f31c
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/managing-logs.en.rst:105
msgid "Rolled Log Filename Format"
msgstr ""

# 884bcb7a712c4746871a9bf0d2218581
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/managing-logs.en.rst:107
msgid ""
"|TS| provides a consistent naming scheme for rolled log files that "
"enables you to easily identify log files. When |TS| rolls a log file, it "
"saves and closes the old file before it starts a new file. |TS| renames "
"the old file to include the following information:"
msgstr ""

# 2950c02cedcf4c8faac06b350ff9f5d6
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/managing-logs.en.rst:112
msgid "The format of the file (such as ``squid.log``)."
msgstr ""

