#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/managing-logs.en.rst:182
msgid "The offset hour, which is an hour between ``0`` (midnight) and ``23``."
msgstr ""

# cbc5a6853d2b4910a14e69456f916436
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/managing-logs.en.rst:184
msgid "The rolling interval."
msgstr ""

# 1a5d3355b83e455ea1c2f7a575f2cac7
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/managing-logs.en.rst:186
msgid ""
"Both the offset hour and the rolling interval determine when log file "
"rolling starts. Rolling occurs every *rolling interval* and at the "
"*offset* hour. For example, if the rolling interval is six hours and the "
"offset hour is ``0`` (midnight), then the logs will roll at midnight "
"(00:00), 06:00, 12:00, and 18:00 each day. If the rolling interval is 12 "
"hours and the offset hour is ``3``, then logs will roll at 03:00 and "
"15:00 each day."
msgstr ""

